## IsKeyDown

*IsKeyDown* will return *Success* if a given key is currently pressed or *Failure* if not. Key is a key on your physical or virtual keyboard. Use *IsButtonDown* to check if a button on your Siri / Apple TV remote is pressed.

Syntax:

`IsKeyDown<Key: "KeyName">`

The name of the keys are the same name as on your keyboard, like "W" or "F", special case have description names, like "ArrowUp", "Space" and "Return".

*IsKeyDown* is only available on devices with a keyboard. If no keyboard is present it returns *Failure*.
